@0=~BLIZZARD IN BAATOR

^NNOTE: This zombie allows you to start playing the Blizzard in Baator expansion mod immediately. You will receive experience points to level up, choose your class and alignment, and obtain some basic equipment. Thanks to this, you will be able to begin the mod's storyline without having to reach the point in the game where it normally starts, which is just before the conclusion of the Nameless One's story.^-
~
@1=~^NIt is recommended to play Planescape: Torment from the beginning. This allows Blizzard in Baator's content to blend into the original storyline more organically. The zombie is an imperfect shortcut for demonstration purposes.^-~
@2=~A grotesque living corpse sways back and forth like a leaf in the wind. A tattooed number adorns its forehead: #000. That alone makes you feel uneasy. Something does not add up. As you approach the zombie, it gestures for you to stop and touches your forehead with its ragged, rotten hand. Suddenly, you experience a sense of déjà vu, accompanied by a tingling sensation at the back of your head and a flood of memories from the past.~
@4=~Allow your mind to be flooded with memories.  ^NUse the shortcut.^-~
@5=~Modify your party.~
@6=~"What else do you have for me, zombie?"~
@7=~Leave.~
@9=~A flood of questions enters your mind, some of which seem important. You struggle with the abundance of intrusive thoughts, but after a moment's reflection, you manage to organize them. Even though you are just talking to a zombie, the questions feel as though they are coming from the deepest recesses of your own mind. ~ [SPTR_01]
@10=~"A person's profession and personality often define them. What principles have guided your life? What was your occupation?"~
@12=~"Only the strongest will prevail. I was a fighter."~
@13=~"I was guided by knowledge and I trusted in the Art. I was a mage."~
@14=~"A knife in the back? I'm no stranger to it. I was a thief."~
@16=~"What ideas guided your path?"~
@18=~"Honor and duty." (Lawful Good)~
@19=~"Empathy and altruism." (Neutral Good)~
@20=~"Freedom for me and others." (Chaotic Good)~
@21=~"Law and order." (Lawful Neutral)~
@22=~"Balance in all things." (True Neutral)~
@23=~"My own freedom of action." (Chaotic Neutral)~
@24=~"My will, which should be law for others." (Lawful Evil)~
@25=~"My profit and pleasure." (Neutral Evil)~
@26=~"My whim and expediency." (Chaotic Evil)~
@28=~"Morte mentioned a name: Pharod. He also menioned a journal. Or were they multiple journals?" The zombie's hand tightens around your head.~
@30=~"Hmm. I've updated my journal."~
@32=~"You met an angel. First, he was imprisoned, and then you fought him in battle. What happened?"~
@34=~"I convinced him to seek redemption."~
@35=~"I convinced him to seek redemption... but Vhailor killed him anyway."~
@36=~"I did nothing to stop him."~
@37=~"He died by my hand."~
@38=~"Vhailor killed him."~
@40=~In Sigil, your faction affiliation reflects your beliefs and convictions. It also affects how you are perceived by society. "Did you belong to a faction?" You remember belonging to...~
@42=~"None of them."~
@43=~"The Revolutionary League, the Anarchists."~
@44=~"The Dustmen."~
@45=~"The Believers of the Source, the Godsmen."~
@46=~"The Society of Sensation, the Sensates."~
@47=~"The Xaositects."~
@49=~Somewhere around here, on one of the graves, a name is carved into a catafalque: Deionarra. It is a name that feels insistently familiar. You remember her apparition appearing as you approach the grave. She tells you about portals and your immortality. You remember how to resurrect the dead and many other things. You promise her that you will either save her or join her. She forgives you for your past mistakes. ~ [SPTR_01]
@51=~"But can I ever forgive myself?"~
@53=~"You had companions in your torment... You remember them. Who was among them?"~
@55=~"Dak'kon, a githzerai zerth."~
@56=~"Annah-of-the-Shadows, a tiefling thief."~
@57=~"Ignus, the fire-crazed spellslinger."~
@58=~"Fall-from-Grace, a succubus cleric of the notion of experience itself."~
@59=~"Nordom, the rogue modron."~
@60=~"Vhailor, the haunted Mercykiller armor."~
@61=~Look at the skull. "Morte?"~
@62=~"That's it. Time to head into the multiverse."~
@63=~"What else do you have for me, zombie?"~
@65=~At this point, the zombie pulls a roll of paper out of his apron and hands it to you. It is some kind of magical parchment. You wonder if it carries anything else.~
@66=~^NNOTE: The parchment allows you to skip the Mortuary and proceed with the mod's content. If you are using the shortcut anyway, it is advisable to use the parchment once you have finished fine-tuning your party.^-~
@68=~Open the shop and select items that are appropriate for your character's class, as well as for your companions.~